{
  "texts": [
    "This method can effectively address the feature smoothing problem caused by the high centrality of gene nodes in molecular networks, and thus improve the accuracy and insight of the model in predicting drug synergism.",
    "In protein function prediction, (Jiao et al. 2023) employed a graph convolution network to encode features of amino acid residues of the protein structure, followed by the use of a self-attentive pooling mechanism to distill the entire protein graph-level representation and integrate it with the representation generated by the language model.",
    "This innovative strategy significantly enhances the model's ability to understand the functional properties of proteins.",
    "In the face of the limitations of graph neural networks in protein structure analysis, such as the difficulty in capturing longdistance information and identifying key residues, (Gu et al. 2023) proposed the Hierarchical Graph Transformer (HGT) model to achieve effective capture of long-range structural relationships in protein graphs through the introduction of motif super-nodes.",
    "Meanwhile, the attention pooling technique is used to aggregate these super-nodes to generate more representative graph-level representations, which provides a powerful tool for an in-depth understanding of the importance of local functional motifs in proteins."
  ]
}